{"title":"Can’t upload files in Safari? Update to Safari 14.0.3 (or drag and drop)","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/3605730/cant-upload-files-in-safari-update-to-safari-1403-or-drag-and-drop.html#tk.rss_all","date":1612526400000,"content":"<article>\n\t<section class=\"page\">\n<p>Wth the release of Safari 14.0.1 for macOS last November, Apple introduced a bug that prevented the use of the “upload files” option on web pages. The problem persisted until February 1, 2021, when the company released the 14.0.3 update for all supported macOS releases. If you’ve had this problem, simply update Safari to make it go away.</p><figure class=\"medium right\"><a class=\"zoom\" href=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/mac911-drag-file-onto-button-100875846-orig.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/mac911-drag-file-onto-button-100875846-medium.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"mac911 drag file onto button\" width=\"300\" height=\"286\" data-imageid=\"100875846\" data-license=\"IDG\"/></a> <small class=\"credit\">IDG</small>\n<figcaption>\n<p>Drag a file onto an upload button, and it inverts; release, and the file name or list should be shown.</p><p class=\"jumpTag\"><a href=\"/article/3605730/cant-upload-files-in-safari-update-to-safari-1403-or-drag-and-drop.html#jump\">To read this article in full, please click here</a></p></section></article>","author":"Glenn Fleishman","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"cdf5132e3709b864f93f45284d629868c537a95ea6d5143baf81260910b1cff2","category":"Apple"}